About Me

Home | Research | Publications | Outreach | About | Blog | Gallery

I am originally from Northern Virginia and received my Bachelor’s degrees in Plant Biology and Biological Oceanography from NC State University, where I was mentored by many great scientists, including Drs. Astrid Schnetzer, Brian Langerhans, and Becky Irwin, who inspired me to pursue science. I’m currently pursuing my PhD in Organismic & Evolutionary Biology with Dr. Lynn Adler at UMass Amherst.

I enjoy being in nature, growing plants, and biking. I try to approach life and science with the “Scout Mindset”, devised and explained by philosopher Julia Galef. Feel free to contact me: aefowler [at] umass.edu. I am also on Twitter and Instagram. Please contact me if you would like a copy of my CV.
